Package de.bpmnaftool.model.bpmn.flowobject

Package for FlowObjects, contains interfaces and classes for Activities, Events and Gateways

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Activity The Activity object represents an activity of a BMPN model.
Event An Event is a FlowObject which can be triggered for various reasons (see trigger attribute).
FlowObject Representation of a Flow Object which is a Activity, Event or Gateway.
Gateway A Gateway is a FlowObject which is used to specify the outgoing SequeceFlow, therefore it may have more than one outgoing SequenceFlow.
 

Class Summary
ActivityImpl Implementing class for an Activity.
EventImpl Implementing class for an Event.
FlowObjectImpl Implementing base class for flow objects
GatewayImpl Implementing base class for Gateway.
GatewayJoin A GatewayJoin is a Gateway which is allowed to have more than one incoming sequence flows.
GatewaySplit A GatewaySplit is Gateway which is allowed to have more than one outgoing sequence flows.
 

Enum Summary
Event.Trigger Defines how the event is triggered.
Event.Type Type of the event.
Gateway.Type Defines the split behavior of this Gateway.
